The paper deals with algorithm selection, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the use of benchmark suites and meta-models, which are common in data science (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for feature representation, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
